# Build-scoped ignore file for pystreams/Dockerfile.pystreams. BuildKit prefers
# "<dockerfile>.dockerignore" over a root .dockerignore, so this keeps the
# pystreams image's context minimal without affecting any other build.
#
# Patterns are evaluated against the build context root (the repo root).

# Start by excluding everything, then allow only what the uv workspace build
# needs: the root lock + workspace manifest, and the two member directories.
*

!pyproject.toml
!uv.lock
!infra
!pystreams

# Trim the infra member down to just its Python wheel inputs (the hatchling
# wheel only packages gram_infra + gen_py). The rest of infra/ is the Go service
# and is never imported by pystreams.
infra/cmd
infra/gen
infra/internal
infra/pkg
infra/proto
infra/main.go

# Local virtualenvs are platform-specific and must be rebuilt in the image.
**/.venv

# Caches and build artifacts.
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.mypy_cache

# Local-only / editor / VCS noise that may live inside the allowed members.
**/.claude
**/.git
**/.gitignore
